{
  "texts": [
    "Two primary methods for identifying COVID-19 have been implemented to track the spread of the disease quickly.",
    "The first is a traditional lab-based test involving symptomatic patients categorized from a healthcare facility.",
    "Symptomatic individuals are typically tested with quick antibody tests at the facility level, which can detect the presence of the virus but do not confirm a positive diagnosis.",
    "Real-time reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) with a nasal or throat swab was used to test suspected individuals who tested negative.",
    "Suspected individuals may be quarantined for two days and then tested again with an antigen test without the real-time RT-PCR test."
  ]
}